This was one of those stories that really stuck with me. Congrats to @EricBoodman, but more importantly, I hope this award brings more readers to this piece, which did much to highlight the inequity in who has been hurt most by #Covid. https://t.co/GKHNBSyjQe

A survey on 1949 vaxxed adults run by Survivor Corp (so, there is likely a bias towards people who have long-term effects from Covid.) 

But as @dianaberrent points out, CDC isn't tracking "mild" symptomatic breakthrough cases so we don't have national unbiased data. https://t.co/aEhjQtiOcl
@ConnConnection @CDCgov Indeed! and it's frustrating how poorly understood #LongCovid is, still, from risk factors to treatment.

Good read on how to think about #Delta & breakthrough infections post #CovidVaccine. 

I agree with the author that one's personal risk tolerance is a big factor AND people need good info to make wise decisions.
